  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Trade Finance Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>This role supports regional trading activities by managing trade finance instruments, overseeing payment flows, and ensuring effective working capital management. The position is highly documentation-driven and involves regular coordination with banks, internal teams, and external counterparties to meet transaction timelines and compliance standards.</strong></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Execute end-to-end trade finance transactions, including Letters of Credit (LCs), Standby LCs, Bank Guarantees, and Bills of Exchange.</li><li>Act as the main point of contact with banks on document submission, negotiation, and settlement matters.</li><li>Review trade documentation to ensure alignment with UCP 600, ISBP, Incoterms, and applicable international trade rules.</li><li>Track payment movements, manage reconciliations, and proactively resolve discrepancies.</li><li>Partner with sales, procurement, and logistics teams to ensure financial documents are consistent with shipment and contract requirements.</li><li>Monitor utilisation of banking facilities and prepare cash flow and funding projections.</li><li>Provide timely management reporting on trade finance activities and exposures.</li><li>Assist with audit reviews and ensure proper documentation of trade and banking transactions.</li><li>Keep abreast of regulatory developments, sanctions requirements, and evolving banking practices.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Finance, Accounting, Business, or a related field.</li><li>3–5 years of hands-on experience in trade finance, preferably within commodities or steel trading environments.</li><li>Solid understanding of UCP 600, ISBP, Incoterms, and SWIFT processes.</li><li>Comfortable working with Excel and financial systems; ERP exposure is a plus.</li><li>Highly detail-focused, structured, and able to manage multiple deadlines simultaneously.</li><li>Confident communicator who works well with both internal stakeholders and external banking partners.</li></ul><p><strong>Reg No. R1980724</strong></p><p><strong>Triton AI Pte Ltd</strong></p><p><strong>License no. 21C0661</strong></p>",
